## What Changed

Realizer interrogation surfaces readiness gaps (e.g. `missing_foundation`, `stale_activity`).
Previously the UI showed a generic explanation paragraph. This session established that each gap
should map to a **specific WAI skill command** that fixes it:

| Gap | Skill |
|-----|-------|
| `missing_foundation`, `missing_goals`, `missing_stage` | `/wai-foundation` |
| `missing_state_file`, `spoke_not_found` | `/wai-init-v2` |
| `stale_activity` | `/wai-closeout` |

The command is shown directly on the page as the primary CTA — one line, copy button, no paragraph.

## Why It Matters

Users asked "what do I do?" when a spoke was blocked. A generic list of file edits is arcane.
A specific skill command they can paste into Claude Code is immediately actionable.

## Recommended Framework Improvement

Add `suggested_skill` field to the lug schema. When a Realizer fix-task lug arrives in a spoke's
inbox, the wakeup protocol should surface the `suggested_skill` as the first recommended action —
so the user is directed automatically without needing to look at Realizer.

```json
{
  "id": "task-analysing-local-mcp-realizer-remediate-missing_foundation-v1",
  "type": "task",
  "suggested_skill": "/wai-foundation",
  ...
}
```

## Prerequisites

```bash
# Verify gap-to-skill map exists in realizer UI
grep -n "GAP_SKILL" web/templates/realizer.html | head -5
```

